The point is, in a complex brain, real thinking is possible, but in a simple brain, only 'bouncing around between a few variables' is possible, which is not capable of solving most problems, which require 10 or 100 or 1000 variables.
You can see that this over-simplicity is why people are racist/biased toward similarity (themselves), for example. This brain doesn't have an imagination/simulation so it gets everything wrong unless the problem requires a 'simple physical change to a simple physical structure', bc it can't support functions like 'empathize/derive', as it has no extra parameters that enable those functions.
